
## Kafka

### install
> brew install kafka // dependency zookeeper included

### Start included zookeeper
> zookeeper-server-start <kafka-install-root-dir>/libexec/config/zookeeper.properties
This is a link to zookeeper config file stored at /usr/local/etc/kafka, including where data reside and which port it uses.

### Start kafka server
> kafka-server-start <kafka-install-root-dir>/libexec/config/server.properties

### Otherwise, you can use brew services to start/stop these two
> brew services start zookeeper
> brew services start kafka

Now you are ready to use https://kafka.apache.org/quickstart
